content: I wanted early music temperaments and a wide range of A frequencies. I found them here with a nice screen showing my actual pitches in reference to the 12 chromatic tones. Actually that gets to the one inadequacy of this (and every other) tuning app. The idea of 12 chromatic steps is an equal temperament outcome that should not be imposed on other temperaments. A whole step really being 9 commas, such that a minor half-step is 4 and a major is 5. Thus a G# is a comma lower than an Aflat.

content: can't live without it now
Fun and useful

I love this tuner. The wide variety of drones, use of chords, and different subdivisions are great. The only thing I wish it had (and the only reason I have a 2nd metronome app installed) is a tempo trainer. Basically you give a starting tempo, ending tempo, time signature, and a time. Then over that interval of time it'll slowly increase the tempo from 1 tempo to the goal tempo. It's really great for practicing.

I really wish this app were updated. The iOS version had a few really nice tweaks that were supposed to come to Android... But the last update was over 4 years ago...
